This paper deals with the analysis of graph algorithms and their performance in different metrics. The focus is on the stretch factor of the Yao graph, which is a well-studied topic in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Systems and Control).
